All Implemented Interfaces:
Cursor
public class BaseSelectionFilterCursor
extends BaseFilterCursor

Creates a subset of an existing Cursor that must be filtered by a SelectionSet. All Data in the Cursor must be Features. You can choose between the following two methods of filtering,

  • Features in the Cursor must belong to the SelectionSet - results in an intersect operation, or
  • Features in the Cursor must not belong to the SelectionSet - results in an xor operation.
